{"TopicId":147898,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Loosing one of the vessels after separation during atmospheric flight","CreatedByName":"wfox","CreatedById":168855,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T23:18:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"wfox","CreatedById":168855,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T23:18:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have constructed an air-launched rocket-plane, which launches from the mother ship (think X15 that launches from B52)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter separation I can switch between the ships just fine with [ ], but only as long as the distance between them is less than 20km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter that, non-selected vessel vanishes\u00A0from the map completely, like it never existed. It does not crash and remains functional, just vanishes along with the crew.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this a bug or missing feature?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Waseemq1235","CreatedById":159178,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-17T06:51:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo wonder you lose boosters even when parachuting them...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s actually the limit for KSP, there is no in-game vanilla way of extending the range.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are looking for a mod that can fix it, then it\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:14px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Eis the Lazor system mod by Romfarer,\u00A0Bear in mind that Lazor adds a lot of other parts and windows, if you like stock it might not be for you.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:14px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EEdit: Lazor system is actually outdated, only works for .90\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-size:14px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u00A0I have not clue on how to extend the range.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-17T06:53:38Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2016 06:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Waseemq1235\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalBuzzsaw","CreatedById":158329,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-17T08:40:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBDA does it, so it SHOULD be possible\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wfox","CreatedById":168855,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-17T16:31:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo bad, I was thinking there is a way to extend the \u0027bubble\u0027 enough to let the boosters land.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBDA is BDArmory right? (sorry, I am complete noob to the Kerbal space\u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Waseemq1235","CreatedById":159178,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-17T17:48:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222761631\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147898\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474129868\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168855\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wfox\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, wfox said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBDA is BDArmory right? (sorry, I am complete noob to the Kerbal space\u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, but I am not sure if it can extend the destroy range, but I am sure that it extends the physics range (the range which the craft will be affected by physics)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-17T17:48:58Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2016 05:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Waseemq1235\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-28T07:18:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalright, this is a well discussed topic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/76940-ship-just-disappeared/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/app/220200/discussions/0/616187204171428487/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://steamcommunity.com/app/220200/discussions/0/616187204171428487/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasicly every ship/debris/whatsoever further away than 2km in the atmophere will be lost, there are a few mods you can install so you can recover your stages, some very good ones are:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/72605-110-flight-manager-for-reusable-stages-fmrs-x110-experimental/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/78226-112-stagerecovery-recover-funds-from-dropped-stages-v164-050216/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scientia1423","CreatedById":116562,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T08:54:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222760678\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147898\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474067930\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168855\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wfox\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/17/2016 at 0:18 AM, wfox said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter that, non-selected vessel vanishes\u00A0from the map completely, like it never existed. It does not crash and remains functional, just vanishes along with the crew.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWherever that non-selected vessel went, I think it went over the bermuda triangle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s pretty much everywhere O.o\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-08T22:16:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty much this: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/kkfHH#ctOJikL\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/kkfHH#ctOJikL\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}